SFT/checkpoints/
__pycache__/

# ── Model weights and training state ────────────────────────────────────
# These are binary artifacts, regenerable from training code + data. They
# blow up the repo fast (one LoRA checkpoint = ~170 MB of optimizer state
# + ~84 MB of weights) and some are over GitHub's 100 MB hard limit.
# Push them to an HF hub / S3 / Git LFS instead.
*.safetensors
*.pt
*.pth
*.bin
*.ckpt

# Training checkpoint directories written by the HF Trainer. The final
# selected adapter (``lora_best/``) is still picked up by the *.safetensors
# rule above, so if you do want to keep it, explicitly `git add -f`.
sft_8b/results/**/checkpoint-*/

# Bulky tokenizers bundled alongside adapters (~17 MB each); the base
# model's tokenizer is always available from HF.
sft_8b/results/**/tokenizer.json

# llama.cpp / quantization caches
*.gguf

# Structured-CoT run artifacts — keep summaries, ignore bulk traces & logs.
structured_cot/results/**/*.jsonl
structured_cot/results/lsf/
